The paper proposes a framework for dynamical analysis of nonlinear dynamical systems in video-based inference tasks. The proposed framework uses shape distributions of the dynamical attractor as a feature representation of the nature of dynamics. This approach has applications in activity recognition, activity quality assessment, and dynamical scene classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper uses nonlinear dynamical models such as Lorenz and Rossler systems, indicating a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
